div.p:
Considering that these differences belong to those which, pursuant to Article I
                    of the Arbitration Convention concluded by the two high contracting parties on
                    May 2, 1908, and renewed by agreements dated May 9, 1914, March 8, 1919, and
                    February 13, 1924, respectively,

                            Foreign Relations, 1909, p. 442; 
                            ibid., 1915, p. 1099; 
                            ibid., 1919, vol. ii,
                            p. 651; 
                            ibid., 1924, vol. ii,
                            p. 474. might well be submitted to arbitration;

list.item:
Her Majesty the Queen of the Netherlands: Jonkheer Dr. A. C. D. de Graeff,
                        Her Majesty’s Envoy Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary at
                        Washington;
